name: test[config helpconfig without ee  clear && ansible-navigator config --help-config --ee False --ll debug --mode stdout]
output: --version             show program's version number, config file location, configured module search path, module location, executable location and exit
-h, --help            show this help message and exit

-v, --verbose         Causes Ansible to print more debug messages. Adding multiple -v will increase the verbosity, the builtin plugins currently evaluate up to -vvvvvv. A reasonable level to start is -vvv, connection debugging might require -vvvv.
